column1: It was great to be with @Grace4NY @Tom_Suozzi & all the Queens leaders & friends last night. Thank you to Rep. @val_demings for lighting up the zoom!

I’m looking forward to this important #BackToSchool2020  zoom forum for parents and students on Covid-19 tomorrow night at 7pm with Dr. @panagis21 from @hopkinsmedicine and my partners in the community @JSandersNYC @SenJoeAddabbo @Stacey23AD @DRichards13 & @KhaleelAnderson https://t.co/tq69q2xLQl

.@VoteJackie4NY is an immigrant combat veteran educator single mom and public servant running to flip NY-2 on the South Shore of Long Island blue. If you agree that we need her voice in Congress I hope you’ll join me in as part of her team https://t.co/ix3YsfVpMJ https://t.co/ItQThAlUCr
Kids aren't the only ones looking up to professional athletes tonight. My hat is off to the players and coaches standing tall for what is right. https://t.co/MbQMkLjClE
Congrats to the production team @DNC.  The #demconvention was a huge success and we are fired up to elect @joebiden and @kamalaharris Thank you for all your hard work!
If you are in the arena you need to be prepared to take a punch.  You also need to be ready to throw a punch....for the children.  My Speaker @SpeakerPelosi #MadameSpeaker
Such a thrill to watch @KamalaHarris with my wife and daughters last night.  She and @JoeBiden are EXACTLY what our country needs now.  Let's do this!!
Proud to be part of New York delegation casting votes for our next President Joe Biden tonight! #DemConvention #LetsGoJoe https://t.co/zdV1CGUVmd
Let's do the work to get @KamalaHarris and @JoeBiden elected! #BidenHarris2020 @HowardUAlumni
Thrilled by the selection of @KamalaHarris and I can't wait to vote for the first African American Woman first Asian American and first HBCU graduate on a Presidential ticket.

Thank you to EVERYONE who voted early voted by mail or came out yesterday. While it will take time to #CountEveryVote I am humbled by the outpouring of support from my constituents and inspired by the strong turnout in races across New York. Thank you neighbors!

VOTE TODAY Primary Election  Tuesday June 23 2020  Today is the day to let your voices be heard and vote! I encourage each of you to use your strength in numbers and let’s win this!   #Election2020  #Vote #NYPrimary

VOTE TOMORROW  June 23rd is the day to make your voices count! To all our dedicated residents and voters please vote and I hope I that I will have your support.  Let's put Joe Biden and the Biden delegates in office.   In addition please support these great local leaders!!! https://t.co/tIc5pWpJZ1
Vote tomorrow! https://t.co/HfG4Fsg82D
Wishing all Dads a wonderful Father's Day! Thank you for all the ways you go above and beyond for your families. https://t.co/UVFPYh59Nc
She fights like hell for all of us. There is no substitute for leadership and experience. Thank you @CarolynBMaloney for all that you do for New York and America! https://t.co/3YdMb7aAi7

Protesting is a beautiful thing but banging on the door of someone's home is way over the line. Nobody in public life deserves this sort of treatment especially a trailblazer like @Dromm25 https://t.co/zzIc0IX9hh

I am humbled to have the endorsement of the great men and women of DC 37. They have kept our city moving through this pandemic and they have stood on the front lines of every challenge. I am looking forward to continuing our partnership. @DistCouncil37 https://t.co/G94OAnUjhh

My sincerest gratitude to the members of the Hotel Trades Council for their endorsement so many of whom live & work in my district. We will continue the fight for working families – expanding opportunity &  improving working conditions for HTC members and workers everywhere. https://t.co/dAKMqTfaU1
The proud members of the @UFT have always been a great partner in the pursuit of excellence for our children. I am honored to have earned their support for my re-election! https://t.co/tjK5x1zwhv

Mark ‘Temporary Illness’ on the form as the reason you are requesting the ballot - this definition has been temporarily expanded to include both those affected by COVID-19 and/or the potential of contracting the virus. #VoteFromHome

New Yorkers can #VoteByMail by requesting an absentee ballot at https://t.co/pLhFeRSprx or returning the absentee ballot application that will be mailed to every registered voter eligible to vote in the primary. #VoteFromHome

Important nominations being decided June 23 in NYS including Congress State Legislature and Queens Borough President.  Plans are being made for early & in-person voting but I urge everyone to #VoteByMail  #VoteFromHome

@MikeBloomberg @Mike2020 I look forward to working with @MikeBloomberg as we revitalize overlooked communities enable wealth creation for working families close the wealth gap for African Americans and fight against Donald Trump who threatens our fundamental American values every single day. #Mike2020
@MikeBloomberg @Mike2020 As mayor he made promises with concrete plans to see them through. As president he will #GetItDone

@MikeBloomberg @Mike2020 We need someone in the White House who will unite us behind the common purpose of rebuilding our nation’s infrastructure and driving our economy forward. @MikeBloomberg will do exactly that.

I am endorsing @MikeBloomberg in the #DemPrimary because we need a pragmatic leader who will deliver. The most vulnerable communities in America cannot weather another four years of this President. Too much is on the line to allow that to happen. #GetItDone @Mike2020 #Mike2020
